.TH AGENT-HOOK-SESSION-START-CLAUDE 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-session-start-claude \- Claude-specific session-start extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-session-start-claude
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-session-start-claude
is sourced by
.BR agent-hook-session-start (1)
when the active runtime is Claude. It is not a standalone hook adapter and
should not be configured directly as the session-start command.
.PP
The extension runs Claude-specific startup maintenance, such as the quiet daily
Claude template refresh, while the generic hook owns stdin parsing, repository
context, Hive Memory context, extension loading, and final JSON emission.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The extension completed or had no Claude-specific work to do.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agent-hook-session-start (1)
